Package cz.cuni.mff.d3s.deeco.annotations

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IValuedAnnotation
    IValuedAnnotation interface is used to simplify annotation parsing.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnnotationProxy  
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    DEECoComponent
    DEECoComponent annotation is used to mark the class definition as a top level component knowledge.
    DEECoCoordinatorIn
    DEECoCoordinatorIn marks a method parameter as a coordinator input parameter, which is used when evaluating an ensemble.
    DEECoCoordinatorInOut
    DEECoCoordinatorInOut is used to mark a method parameter as both coordinator input and coordinator output parameter, which is used when evaluating an ensemble.
    DEECoCoordinatorOut
    DEECoCoordinatorOut is used to mark a method parameter as a coordinator output parameter for ensemble evaluation.
    DEECoEnsemble
    DEECoEnsemble is used to mark a class as an ensemble definition class.
    DEECoEnsembleMapper
    DEECoEnsembleMapping is used to mark the method in the ensemble definition class as the mapping function.
    DEECoEnsembleMembership
    DEECoEnsembleMembership is used to mark the method in the ensemble definition class as the membership function.
    DEECoInitialize
    DEECoInitialize is used to mark a method in the component knowledge definition class, to be used for initial instance retrieval.
    DEECoMemberIn
    DEECoMemberIn marks a method parameter as a member input parameter, which is used when evaluating an ensemble.
    DEECoMemberInOut
    DEECoMemberInOut is used to mark a method parameter as both member input and member output parameter, which is used when evaluating an ensemble.
    DEECoMemberOut
    DEECoMemberOut is used to mark a method parameter as a member output parameter for ensemble evaluation.
    DEECoPeriodicScheduling
    DEECoPeriodicScheduling is used to mark an ensemble class or a component process to be executed periodically.
    DEECoProcess
    DEECoProcess is used to mark a method to be a component process.
    DEECoProcessIn
    DEECoProcessIn marks a method parameter as a process input parameter, which is used when invoking a component process.
    DEECoProcessInOut
    DEECoProcessInOut is used to mark a method parameter as both process input and process output parameter, which is used when invoking a component process.
    DEECoProcessOut
    DEECoProcessOut is used to mark a method parameter as a process output parameter for a component process evaluation.
    DEECoTriggeredScheduling
    DEECoTriggeredScheduling is used to mark an ensemble class or a component process to be event triggered.
